fields.description: Bougainvillea is a genus of thorny ornamental vines, bushes, and trees belonging to the four o' clock family, Nyctaginaceae.

fields.name: Ox-Eye Daisies
fields.description: Ox-eye daisy is a native wildflower and is a typical grassland perennial wildflower, which grows in meadows, fields, roadsides and often where soils are heavy and damp.

fields.name: Daisies Mixed Set
fields.description: The flower head is a typical daisy shape, with white petals and yellow central florets and is a bushy, generally upright plant.

fields.name: Yellow Roses
fields.description: Yellow roses are a welcome addition to any garden – their colouring seeming to denote happiness and sunshine. Deep yellow roses are ideal for creating contrast in the border whereas soft yellow roses blend beautifully with other roses and plants.

fields.name: Dame Du Coeur Hybrid Tea Rose
fields.description: Dame de Coeur is a cross between the renowned garden rose 'Peace' and 'Independence'. It’s a vigorous grower with healthy dark-green glossy foliage and bears picture perfect deep cherry red large blossoms with an amazing strong fragrance throughout the summer. The fabulous long-lasting huge blooms work great as cut flowers.

fields.name: Pink Roses
fields.description: A light rosy tone is often associated with femininity, so, naturally, the pink rose meaning is that of grace and sweetness. Other interpretations include gentleness, appreciation, joy, thankfulness, and elegance. The variety of meanings make giving pink roses appropriate for so many occasions.

fields.name: 10 pcs white Rose Flower seeds
fields.description: White roses symbolize purity, youthfulness, and innocence. Young love, eternal loyalty, and new beginnings are also commonly tied to the meaning of white roses, making them a popular choice for weddings and romantic occasions.

fields.name: Potted Rose - Stunning Apricot Blooms
fields.description: Lovely Ruffled Apricot Blooms, with a sweet scent. Have a healthy dark green foliage

fields.name: Rosa 'Big Purple
fields.description: This is a compact, upright, hybrid tea rose producing highly fragrant purple flowers from summer into autumn. Repeat flowering. Grows up to 90cm tall.

fields.name: Mixed Rose Set
fields.description: Selection of nine different roses

fields.name: Rose 'Trumpeter' 3.5 Litre
fields.description: Rosa 'Trumpeter' is an extremely compact and healthy, dwarf floribunda rose with large clusters of fully double cupped, bright vermillion red flowers.

fields.name: Lily 'Bright Diamond'
fields.description: Throw a spotlight into your planting plans with groups of this shining star, Asiatic Lily 'Bright Diamond'. It's pure sophistication from top to toe, belting out a fanfare of large, gleaming white blooms on top of strong, sturdy stems.

fields.name: Lilium asiatic Forever Susan
fields.description: Asian lilies are sturdy lilies that grow easily, suitable for perennial plantings in public green spaces. They are characterized by a very wide color spectrum with many hard, bright colors.

fields.name: Hibiscus rosa-sinensis 'Seminole Pink'
fields.description: Bringing the tropics to your garden has never been easier when it comes to the Pink Hibiscus. The Pink Hibiscus bush is a beautiful, exotic evergreen shrub.

fields.name: Honeymoon Deep Red Hibiscus
fields.description: Wide, rounded, overlapping petals are neatly pleated and gently ruffled at the tips, which are slightly darker, as if outlining the bloom for greater effect

fields.name: Exotic Coral Flower Hibiscus
fields.description: You can plant it in home and garden, bonsai, small park, office desk, balcony, courtyard, etc.

fields.name: Hibiscus rosa-sinensis
fields.description: Hibiscus rosa-sinensis is a bushy, evergreen shrub or small tree growing 2.5–5 m (8–16 ft) tall and 1.5–3 m (5–10 ft) wide. The plant has a branched taproot. Its stem is aerial, erect, green, cylindrical, and branched.

fields.name: Hibiscus Starburst Chiffon
fields.description: Each reaching up to 5 inches across and in an exquisite, deeply-veined starburst bicolour of deep pink and white!

fields.name: Yellow Hibiscus
fields.description: The yellow hibiscus ranges in size from a small 2- to 6-foot-tall shrub to a larger 15- to 30-foot-tall tree. The mature plant has a spread of 8 to 10 feet, notes Native Plants Hawaii. The flowers of this species of hibiscus are yellow and fragrance-free with sharp prickles around the base.

fields.name: Hibiscus Yellow Hybrid Double Color
fields.description: . Plants have medium size leaves and large size yellow flowers. They grow to over 2 meters tall. Can be kept short by trimming. Plants are covered daily with big yellow flower. Hibiscus flowers have been popular since centuries. Most hibiscus flowers bloom during the day and close at night.

fields.name: Hibiscus Mixed set
fields.description: Mixture of red, white, yellow and pink hibiscus

fields.name: Hibiscus Syriacus Pink Flirt
fields.description: An upright, multi-stemmed, deciduous shrub. Produces bushy dark-green foliage and trumpet shaped, lilac flowers with deep magenta throats.

fields.name: Red Hibiscus
fields.description: This is a homemade, organic starter plant that has been grown from cuttings and has a well-developed root system. The size of the product may vary between 3 to 8 inches in length.

fields.name: Hibiscus Orange-Yellow Hybrid
fields.description: Hibiscus yellow hybrid bush tree, well rooted plug, 5 plus inches, butterfly bees , extra blooms gorgeous flowers organic gift outdoor

fields.name: Lily (Lilium) Orange Space
fields.description: Lily Orange Space (Orienpet Hybrid Lily 'Orange Space'). Hybrid origin. This bright lily is simply unmatched! It is very similar to the old variety 'Thunderbolt'.

fields.name: Light blue hydrangea
fields.description: Hydrangea macrophylla 'Blue,' commonly known as Blue Hydrangea, is a captivating flowering shrub highly sought after in the Irish climate for its stunning blue blossoms. It is a popular choice among gardeners in Ireland, adding vibrant color and charm to outdoor spaces.

fields.name: Hydrangeas Mixed Set
fields.description: A mixture of pink, purple, white and blue hydrangeas

fields.name: Hydrangea arborescens Pink Annabelle
fields.description: A pink version of the popular hydrangea Annabelle, Hydrangea arborescens Pink Annabelle is a deciduous shrub with a rounded, bushy habit.

fields.name: Hydrangea Macrophylia Purple Dance
fields.description: An upright, bushy, deciduous shrub with broad, dark green leaves and large, spherical clusters of purple flowers.

fields.name: Hydrangea Paniculata 'PINKY WINKY'
fields.description: Hydrangea paniculata 'Pinky Winky' is a sturdy, upright to slightly spreading selection with a compact habit. Foliage is yellow-green, stems are dark purplish-red, maturing to brown. Sterile florets open lime green, then pale to white, turning deep pink at maturity.

fields.name: Lily (Lilium) White County
fields.description: White County is a large plant belonging to the Asian lily group. With its help, demanding gardeners decorate gift bouquets and enjoy the aesthetics.

fields.name: Lily 'Brindisi'
fields.description: The strong pink Lily 'Brindisi' will not let you ignore her in your summer garden, however hard you may try. This impressive lily will display up to seven flowers on each of her sturdy stems, which will make it hard to overlook her completely.

fields.name: Lilies Mixed Set
fields.description: A mixture of red, white, yellow and pink lilies

fields.name: Lily (Lilium) Orange Summer
fields.description: Lily (Lilium) Orange Summer is renowned for its striking, trumpet-shaped blossoms that captivate with their bold and lively orange hue. Each petal seems to glow with warmth and radiance, making it an excellent choice for those looking to make a statement with their floral arrangements.

fields.name: Lily (Lilium) Happy Memories
fields.description: Lily (Lilium) Happy Memories is a captivating variety of lily known for its pristine white petals adorned with speckles of soft pink and a heavenly fragrance that is sure to enchant your senses. The name Happy Memories perfectly encapsulates the emotions this flower evokes – memories of happiness, celebrations, and cherished moments.

fields.name: Lilium asiatic Red Highland
fields.description: Asian lilies are sturdy lilies that grow easily, suitable for perennial plantings in public green spaces. They are characterized by a very wide color spectrum with many hard, bright colors.

fields.name: Lily 'Saltarello'
fields.description: Lily 'Saltarello' is one of the exciting new class of lilies, known as the oriental × trumpet lilies, often seen as orienpets. Their large blooms carry the perfume of the oriental lily, with the strong growth habit of the trumpet lily.

fields.name: Lilium Orange Ton
fields.description: Lilium Orange Ton adds vibrant splashes of color to gardens with its bold blooms and striking presence. This variety showcases large, trumpet-shaped flowers with vivid orange petals, exuding energy and warmth in any landscape.

fields.name: Alstroemeria 'Theresa'
fields.description: Bring a flamboyant pop of colour to summer borders with the sugary, bubble-gum shades of Alstroemeria 'Theresa'. Candy pink petals are splotched with raspberry and dotted with dark magenta freckles that catch the eye even from a distance, drawing you in for a closer look!

fields.name: White with Purple Orchids
fields.description: Inspire creativity and light up your home by mixing the best of a purple and white orchid together. Bright, colourful and elegant, this orchid has a single stem and gorgeous white and purple flowers. Typically, your Phalaenopsis orchid will bloom for around 3 months each year.

fields.name: Lilium speciosum var. rubrum
fields.description: Lilium speciosum var. rubrum is full of flirtatious fun. She casually flips her white flared skirt with little concern, revealing her pink flushed underskirt dotted with dark red polka dots as the skirt curls up and back in a wonderfully cheerful dance.

fields.name: Lily (Lilium) Yellow Bruse
fields.description: Lily (Lilium) Yellow Bruse is renowned for its elegant appearance and radiant color. Its large, trumpet-shaped blooms are a stunning shade of sunny yellow, which symbolizes joy, happiness, and friendship.

fields.name: Peonies Mixed Set
fields.description: A mixture of red, white and pink peonies

fields.name: Pink Peonies
fields.description: Peony pink revelation Sarah Bernhardt is a masterpiece of nature. The huge pink ruffled flowers are enhanced by creamy white petals around the base of each flower. They have a heavenly scent and make wonderful cut flowers

fields.name: Paeonia 'Bowl of Beauty'
fields.description: eony 'Bowl of Beauty' will set your garden ablaze with colour, and provide a delightful fragrance into the bargain. Superb as it opens, the delicate bloom’s larger base petals seem to form a chalice for the abundance of small bright yellow petals that crowd together at the centre.

fields.name: Buddyeonia 'Red Sarah Bernhardt'
fields.description: his delightful hardy herbaceous peony is red-flowered, and named after the ever-popular Peony 'Sarah Bernhardt' (which is pale pink). However, this red version, aptly named Peony 'Red Sarah Bernhardt', is really quite unique, and has no obvious similarity, apart from the name.

fields.name: Gloriosa Daisies
fields.description: Gloriosa Daisy is a tetraploid cultivar of Black-Eyed Susan. It has large, yellow flowers with orange, bronze or burgundy centers. Plants are annual to short-lived perennials and bloom mid-summer to early fall.

fields.name: Red Tulips
fields.description: A truly late flowering Tulip (May) with remarkably large dark red flowers that shine slightly. Long flowering time and long-lasting colour. A good tall garden tulip that combines well with other single late Tulips such as Queen of Night and Menton.

fields.name: Tulips Mixed Set
fields.description: A mixture of yel, red and purple tulips

fields.name: Anemone 'Mistral Blu
fields.description: Shake up your style with this gorgeous new Italian Anemone 'Mistral® Blu', quite possibly one of the most intense and vivid blues available, hightened with a subtle hint of mauve for extra oomph.
